        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 4:29PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Salem, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, blowing dust, and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hatch, Rincon, Salem, Rinconcito, Angostura, Plactias, Rodey, and
Peaceful Valley.

This includes Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 26 and
48.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
